  "texts": [
    "The bi-level objective in Eq.",
    "( 4) is approximated by matching the model gradients at each training step t. In this way, the training trajectory on condensed data can mimic that on the original data, i.e., the models trained on these two datasets converge to similar solutions.",
    "The optimization objective L cond in Eq.",
    "( 2) is defined as:L cond = E θ0∼Θ T t=1 D ∇ θ L T (θ t), ∇ θ L S (θ t) s.t.",
    "θ t+1 = opt L S (θ t),(6)where opt (•) is the model parameter optimizer and the parameter of relay model is updated only on S.Trajectory matching."
